<br>
 But to respond to her I would say that:<br>
get the masks in this order as per your level and difficulty to obtain.<br>
<br>
 1. Dark Elf mask in lower guk,no drop,  ask zone if its camped and then ask to loot it if it drops if there isnt a waiting list =) lvl 30-60 zone<br>
<br>
 2. Erudite mask is in howling stones, but it can be purchased in auctions for approx. 3-4k zone lvl is 45-60<br>
<br>
 3. Iksar Hide mask drops in Traks tooth zone, but can be also purchased for 3-4k zone lvl is 40-60<br>
<br>
 4. Vah Shir mask drops in Ssra TEmple, no drop, from the assasin, lvl of zone is 58-60, but i have seen people get this mask at even lower lvls than that. this doesnt look like a mask when looted, it looks like a stone FYI.<br>
<br>
 5. Halfing Mask drops in Chardok off the Overseer named mob deep inside, its no drop, <br>
<br>
 6. Gnome mask,  not! no drop, you can buy this from someone if you are lucky, used to drop in ST from the warders<br>
<br>
 7. High Elf Mask, no drop, this mask is part of the Ragebringer Quest, you need to complete almost the whole quest up to getting the  box to spawn the general. and when he spawns you give general the head from Stanos in HH.<br>
<br>
 8. Barbarian Mask, not! no drop, this can be bought, but highly doubtful, because this drops from the AoW, avatar of war in Kael zone. <br>
<br>
I think thats all the masks so far, unless you consider the Ugly stick. Illusion Troll, LOL<br>
